name: Node-RED MediRdv - README
info:
This Flow demonstrates how to create
a simple frontend webpage with Node-RED.

The public facing page consists of the 
client side JavaScript, CSS and HTML. 

The important technique is how the mustache 
templates are used. Each template will set the
"property" relative to the content. 

The CSS node sets the "msg.payload.style" property.
The JavaScript node sets the "msg.payload.script" property.

The HTML node then includes these properties 
<script>{{{payload.script}}}</script>
<style>{{{payload.style}}}</style>

CREATE TABLE Admin
(
  idAdmin    INTEGER      NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  nomAdmin   VARCHAR(20)  NOT NULL,
  emailAdmin VARCHAR(30)  NOT NULL,
  motDePasse VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (idAdmin)
);

ALTER TABLE Admin
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_idAdmin UNIQUE (idAdmin);

ALTER TABLE Admin
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_emailAdmin UNIQUE (emailAdmin);

CREATE TABLE Horaire
(
  idHoraire INTEGER NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  heure     TIME    NOT NULL,
  idMedecin INTEGER NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (idHoraire)
);

ALTER TABLE Horaire
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_idHoraire UNIQUE (idHoraire);

CREATE TABLE Medecin
(
  idMedecin     INTEGER        NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  nomMedecin    VARCHAR(30)    NOT NULL,
  prenomMedecin VARCHAR(20)    NULL    ,
  emailMedecin  VARCHAR(30)    NOT NULL,
  sexe          ENUM('M', 'F') NOT NULL,
  specialite    VARCHAR(20)    NOT NULL,
  numTel        INTEGER        NULL    ,
  motDePasse    VARCHAR(20)    NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (idMedecin)
);

ALTER TABLE Medecin
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_idMedecin UNIQUE (idMedecin);

ALTER TABLE Medecin
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_emailMedecin UNIQUE (emailMedecin);

CREATE TABLE Medicament
(
  idMedoc   INTEGER      NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  nomMedoc  VARCHAR(20)  NOT NULL,
  descMedoc VARCHAR(100) NULL    ,
  pu        INTEGER      NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (idMedoc)
);

ALTER TABLE Medicament
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_idMedoc UNIQUE (idMedoc);

ALTER TABLE Medicament
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_nomMedoc UNIQUE (nomMedoc);

CREATE TABLE Ordonnance
(
  idOrd     INTEGER      NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  descOrd   VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  medocs    JSON         NOT NULL,
  date      DATETIME     NOT NULL,
  idPatient INTEGER      NOT NULL,
  idMedecin INTEGER      NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (idOrd)
);

ALTER TABLE Ordonnance
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_idOrd UNIQUE (idOrd);

CREATE TABLE Patient
(
  idPatient     INTEGER        NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  nomPatient    VARCHAR(30)    NOT NULL,
  prenomPatient VARCHAR(30)    NULL    ,
  dateNaissance DATE           NULL    ,
  sexe          ENUM('M', 'F') NOT NULL,
  numTel        INTEGER        NULL    ,
  emailPatient  VARCHAR(30)    NOT NULL,
  address       VARCHAR(50)    NULL    ,
  motDePasse    VARCHAR(20)    NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (idPatient)
);

ALTER TABLE Patient
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_idPatient UNIQUE (idPatient);

ALTER TABLE Patient
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_emailPatient UNIQUE (emailPatient);

CREATE TABLE Rdv
(
  idRdv     INTEGER                                            NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  active    BOOLEAN                                            NOT NULL DEFAULT true,
  status    ENUM('ACCEPTER', 'REFUSER',  'ATTENTE', 'ANNULER') NOT NULL DEFAULT 'ATTENTE',
  idHoraire INTEGER                                            NOT NULL,
  dateTime  DATETIME                                           NOT NULL,
  idPatient INTEGER                                            NOT NULL,
  idMedecin INTEGER                                            NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (idRdv)
);

ALTER TABLE Rdv
  ADD CONSTRAINT UQ_idRdv UNIQUE (idRdv);

ALTER TABLE Ordonnance
  ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Medecin_TO_Ordonnance
    FOREIGN KEY (idMedecin)
    REFERENCES Medecin (idMedecin);

ALTER TABLE Horaire
  ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Medecin_TO_Horaire
    FOREIGN KEY (idMedecin)
    REFERENCES Medecin (idMedecin);

ALTER TABLE Rdv
  ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Horaire_TO_Rdv
    FOREIGN KEY (idHoraire)
    REFERENCES Horaire (idHoraire);

ALTER TABLE Rdv
  ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Patient_TO_Rdv
    FOREIGN KEY (idPatient)
    REFERENCES Patient (idPatient);

ALTER TABLE Rdv
  ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Medecin_TO_Rdv
    FOREIGN KEY (idMedecin)
    REFERENCES Medecin (idMedecin);

ALTER TABLE Ordonnance
  ADD CONSTRAINT FK_Patient_TO_Ordonnance
    FOREIGN KEY (idPatient)
    REFERENCES Patient (idPatient);
